\[\begin{cases}  f(x) = 2x, \qquad\qquad \mathrm{if} \quad 0 \leq x \leq \frac{1}{2};\\  f(x) = 2-2x, \qquad \mathrm{if} \quad \frac{1}{2} < x \leq 1.  \end{cases}\]Let $f^{[2]}(x) = f(f(x))$, and $f^{[n + 1]}(x) = f^{[n]}(f(x))$ for each integer $n \geq 2$.
